Title: SPACETIME COARSE GRAININGS IN RELATIVISTIC PARTICLE MOTION  
Author: JOHN T. WHELAN 
Address: Santa Barbara, California 93106-9530, USA  
Affiliation: Department of Physics, University of California,  
Abstract: Hartle's generalized quantum mechanics formalism is used to examine a simple spacetime coarse graining, i.e., a set of alternatives defined with respect to regions extended in time as well as space, in the quantum mechanics of a free relativistic particle. For suitable initial conditions, tractable formulas are found for branch wave functions. Some initial conditions are found to give decoherence and allow the consistent assignment of probabilities. 
